  "texts": [
    "We would like to add this: not only are citizens entitled to keep \"true facts about themselves to themselves\", but also accurate or inaccurate predictions, which can affect the judgment of others.",
    "It has been powerfully argued that AI renders the secret ballot ineffective because it becomes possible to make finegrained electoral predictions with a high level of accuracy (Mainz et al. 2024).",
    "A prediction about someone's voting behaviour gives you a window into their private world-how they wish the future to be for themselves and their loved ones, what is their conception of justice, who is the target of their (un)justified animosity.",
    "For some individuals, political preferences are constitutive of their identity and selfunderstanding, similarly to religion.",
    "This is not true for all data."
  ],
